The course will cover four main topic areas:
d80 1
a80 134
<ul>
  <li> <a href="CS39C.sp97.html">History of Communications Infrastructures</a>,
  <li> <a href="Comp/comp_history.html">History of Computing</a>,
  <li> <a href="Societal/societal_index.html">Societal Impact of
       Computing and Communication</a>,  
  <li> Mobile Computing: The Convergence of Computing and Communication
       <b>(still under construction)</b>.
</ul>

<h3>Discussion Topic Sequence</h3>

The topic areas are divided into 24 "mini-topics".  We'll cover two
"mini-topics" during each 90 minute class meeting.  You'll prepare for
each meeting by reading the 
background material, and during class we'll spend about 15-20 minutes
highlighting key points from the reading, followed by 20-25 minutes of
discussion. 
